SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 576
By Akbari
A RESOLUTION to recognize Tau Iota Sigma, the Memphis
Alumni Chapter of Phi Beta Sigma Fraternity, on
its ninetieth anniversary.
WHEREAS, we take great pleasure in recognizing those exemplary organizations whose
unwavering commitment to social responsibility and public service greatly benefit their
communities and the State of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, one such organization is the Tau Iota Sigma Chapter of Phi Beta Sigma
Fraternity, the Memphis Alumni Chapter, which is celebrating the ninetieth anniversary of its
founding this year; and
WHEREAS, Phi Beta Sigma Fraternity was established at Howard University in
Washington, D.C., on January 9, 1914, by A. Langston Taylor, Leonard F. Morse, and Charles I.
Brown, who set out to establish a Greek letter fraternity that would embody the principles of
brotherhood, scholarship, and service in a unique and impactful way; and
WHEREAS, the Tau Iota Sigma Chapter of Phi Beta Sigma Fraternity is the Memphis
Alumni Chapter and was chartered on June 7, 1935, by Dr. C.S. Jones, Jessie D. Springer, A.B.
Bland, T.O. Fuller, and Louis B. Hobson; and
WHEREAS, over the past ninety years, the chapter has sought to build a mechanism to
deliver services to the general community with every member committed to gaining skills to be
utilized to serve their community as exhibited by the Fraternity's motto, "Culture for Service and
Service for Humanity"; and
WHEREAS, the Tau Iota Sigma Chapter has been a beacon of inspiration in the
Memphis community through its four main programs: Bigger and Better Business, Education,
Social Action, and Sigma Beta Clubs. These programs have made a tangible difference in the
lives of the people of Memphis; and
SJR0576
010753
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Tau Iota Sigma Chapter's sustained commitment to excellence and
humanitarian service exemplifies the core values of Phi Beta Sigma Fraternity, and its
contributions to the State of Tennessee should be recognized on this most auspicious occasion;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend the members of Tau Iota
Sigma, the Memphis Alumni Chapter of Phi Beta Sigma Fraternity, for their outstanding
achievements in community service, congratulate them on their ninetieth anniversary, and
extend to them our best wishes for every continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
